cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CL, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the presence and influence of disinformation spreading on online social networks (Twitter) in the context of the 2019 European Parliament elections. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper analyzes the behavior of users and disinformation outlets on Twitter. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper may use natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of tweets and news articles. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is relevant as the paper may discuss the security implications of disinformation spreading on social networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the use of encryption or other security measures by disinformation outlets.
